Toslink extension: getSigmaTCPSettings() returns `undefined` when
/etc/sigmatcp.conf does not exist (readConfiguration in dsp-programs has no
explicit return value for the file-missing case). The startup handler then
read `.server` on it and threw an uncaughtException. As long as the toslink
extension was not loaded at all (missing cardFeature "toslink"), this went
unnoticed. Now: a defensive null check so the startup listener run completes
deterministically.

--- a/beo-extensions/toslink/index.js
+++ b/beo-extensions/toslink/index.js
@@ -63,7 +63,7 @@
 			if (beo.extensions["dsp-programs"] && beo.extensions["dsp-programs"].getSigmaTCPSettings) {
 				configuration = beo.extensions["dsp-programs"].getSigmaTCPSettings();
-				if (configuration.server &&
+				if (configuration && configuration.server &&
 					configuration.server.lgsoundsync &&
 					configuration.server.lgsoundsync == 1 &&
 					!configuration.server.lgsoundsync.comment) {
